My biggest personal takeaway from this Mina cosplay is to quit sizing up the details. Is the sentiment there? Absolutely. Relatively similar colors? Yes. Is the hat too tall? Yup. Is the embroidery exact? Nope. Did I seriously just make a well-fitted, fully lined jacket?🤯…I decided that even if no one even knew who Mina was, they might look at this as a memorable Victorian costume, and I am totally happy with that! That’s the genre I want to be in— memorable RenFaire, 18th century, and Victorian costumes 🥰 Excited for the next project! Likely 18th century…😄💋💐🎀
.
.

Whew what a year! I cant believe I made 19 costumes 😲 What’s my secret? Two things: 1) Good time mananagement. I literally maintain a tracker 6 months out, day by day, of my costume goals. Life happens and I don’t always follow it, but it helps me stay focused. 2) Sewing every day. That may sound a little extreme, but I make time every single day (except when traveling). Even if it’s just an hour while streaming a show in the evening. I set little goals, and they add up! Plus, I’ve gotten a bit faster and efficient after about 10 years of active costume making 😂🤷🏻‍♀️ I worked with a lot of amazing photographers too!
